e time-varying expected risk under diminishing step sizes and mild mixing conditions. The algorithm achieves O(T) time per iteration and O(√T log T) space complexity, matching the efficiency of state-of-the-art methods while offering superior adaptability. NRDA-OL advances the theory and practice of online learning by introducing principles from non-reversible MCMC and geometric optimization into pairwise settings, enabling robust performance in real-world applications such as adaptive recommender systems, streaming anomaly detection, and lifelong learning platforms where both data and objectives evolve continuously.",
